      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a driver-focused machine featuring the 3.6L M96 power plant with VarioCam Plus. The engine delivers a linear torque curve, sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical highlights include a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent cooling system overhaul. The chassis retains excellent torsional rigidity, and the hydraulic steering rack offers the unfiltered feedback modern EPAS systems lack. Equipped with four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors, the braking performance remains fade-resistant. The exterior shows honest patina, but the mechanical vitals are dialed in for spirited apex-clipping. A solid, high-performance example for the discerning enthusiast.",
